g controls." report said responsibility pilot co-pilot remember remove goggles case, even though wasn't checklist takeoff. air force said c-130j hercules cost $48.5 million per aircraft. pentagon identified airmen killed crash capt. jonathan j. golden, 33, camarillo, california; capt. jordan b. pierson, 28, abilene, texas; staff sgt. ryan d. hammond, 26, moundsville, west virginia; senior airman quinn l. johnson-harris, 21, milwaukee; senior airman nathan c. sartain, 29, pensacola, florida; airman 1st class kcey e. ruiz, 21, mcdonough, georgia. golden, pierson, hammond johnson-harris assigned 39th airlift squadron, dyess air force base, texas. sartain ruiz assigned 66th security forces squadron, hanscom air force base, massachusetts.
